CONCLUSION: A transdiagnostic prevention program, provided in schools, was successful in reducing youth-reported symptoms of anxiety and depression and parent-reported depression. The EMOTION program has the potential to reduce the incidence of anxious and depressive disorders in youth. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2019 APA, all rights reserved).},
